<br>
Fact is that Rogues, Rangers, Knights and Monks have to control their aggro so that the Warriors can hold the mobs attention. The better the aggro weapons the MT has the less active work is required to let him retain aggro. Evades, FD's Jolts and DA's can unload aggro pretty fast, but the obvious factors are Low HP, Proximity and weapon choice. It is largely upto the DPS merchants to allow the MT to MT.<br>
<br>
Since my MT's obtained the likes of BoC it is noticable that I can take more liberties with my DPS on non Luclin mobs and not pull aggro. Enraging blow is not to be underrated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uogbasherfiggbukker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OgbasherFiggbukker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/02 7:59:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1700.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ogbasher.com/kitty.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro</span><hr size=1> as usual this is a good subject, but youre dissecting each part of aggro and trying to say what is more important.<br>
